      Allegro Cozumel
      Cozumel, Mexico

      A splendid resort hotel adjacent to one of the most beautiful sea floors of the Caribbean.

      The Allegro Cozumel**** (4-star) hotel has been designed to offer sophisticated accommodations on the magnificent Playa San Francisco, one of the world’s most beautiful beaches on the island of Cozumel.

      When Jacques Cousteau visited Palancar Reef, he defined it as "paradise." Allegro Cozumel Resort guests can now enjoy it every day thanks to the resort’s proximity. The resort offers excellent packages for diving experiences at one of the world’s top destinations for scuba divers. 

      The hotel boasts spacious suites with a subtle tropical decor and architectural design inspired by tradition and perfect for relaxation. In addition, it offers a superb gastronomic array of 5 restaurants, where guests can recover after a long, active day. 

      The resort provides various leisure and entertainment options both under water, among dolphins and sea turtles, as well as on land, lying in the sand at the beach or next to one of the 5 swimming pools. It also has great facilities for relaxation, such as the U-spa, or for action, such as the water park and the sports area.

      The resort undoubtedly features the perfect amenities to take full advantage of being in paradise with a beach, rainforest and the sea. But above all, it has the sea and one of the most beautiful ocean floors in the world. Because everything has a Caribbean flavor at the Allegro Cozumel.

      Ultimate Dive Experience Program

      The all inclusive Allegro Cozumel offers the best experience in and out of the water. Guests wanting to go diving can use the services provided by the “Ultimate Dive Experience”, and discover the greatest coral reefs in the world.

      Sports and sea activities

      The hotel offers special diving packages at the Palancar reef and a wide range of daytime activities and fabulous sports facilities.

      Incomparable location

      Located near San Francisco, one of the best beaches in Cozumel; the hotel offers a perfect opportunity to explore the wonders of the region.

      Spa

      The hotel has a great wellness zone with treatment services for the guests to pamper their bodies during their stay.

      Transportation service

      The resort has transportation services available for guests, so travel is not an issue.

      Kid’s Club and Water Park

      Families traveling with children will find this area the perfect complement for their children to have fun while they rest.

      Superior Room

      Superior Room

      These spacious and bright 314.31 ft² Superior rooms come equipped with a king size bed or 2 double beds. They all have a balcony with a hammock to relax and contemplate the beautiful scenery. 

      The suites offer a Caribbean ambiance with touches of color and elegant and comfortable furnishings. The suites include a lounge perfect to relax with family or friends.

      Also: Minibar (soda, beer and water), coffee maker and coffee, hair dryer, toiletries, iron and ironing board, safety deposit box, and cot and/or extra bed available upon prior request.

      Family Suite

      Family Suite

      The Family Suite, measuring 380.58 square feet, provides spacious and comfortable accommodation for vacations with the family or with friends. It has two rooms, one with a king bed and the other with two double beds, connected to a spacious living room, where you can relax with your companions, as well as terraces from which to enjoy the beauty of the natural surroundings. The suites also have two fully equipped bathrooms, which include a bathtub and shower for your comfort and total privacy. 

      They are also equipped with a minibar, a microwave oven, a television in each room and another one in the living room with a home theater system, an alarm clock, wireless Internet connection ($), superior toiletries, beach towels and bath robes, cot and/or an extra bed available upon prior request.

      Superior Premium Ultimate Dive Experience - 1 Diver/ 1 non Diver

      Superior Premium Ultimate Dive Experience - 1 Diver/ 1 non Diver

      Superior Premium UDE rooms, measuring 314.31 ft2, offer all the Superior Premium category services, such as a private front desk, a special wristband, an exclusive pool, a free Internet access point, a minibar that is replenished daily, a DVD player in the room and a 32” flat screen TV. 

      In addition, one diving tank per day for one dive, free storage of your equipment in the dive shop, as well as special hangers for wetsuits. These rooms enjoy a privileged location in the resort near the beach and have access to the Santa Rosa lounge with its beautiful sea views, exclusively for UDE guests.

      Pools and amenities

      The hotel has 5 pools, one of which is an aquatic park for children, and a hot tub area for adults facing the beach that has a space with hammocks and is considered to be within the All Inclusive program.

      Previous Next

      Activities and entertainment for the whole family

      The Allegro Cozumel has an excellent entertainment program, but it also has a magnificent kid's club, where children can enjoy the entertainment program designed by qualified entertainment staff while parents can choose to relax on the beach or do their own activities. 

      The Teens Club offers an area fully equipped with games and a rest area. It is perfect to entertain teens. If guests wish, they can also use the babysitting service, for an additional fee. 

      The resort also features a water park with a pirate theme located in one of the children’s pools. A perfect space for little ones to have the most fun for long hours. 

      Every afternoon, guests can attend the theater to enjoy a different show and revel in the great evening entertainment.

      Previous Next

      Sports

      For those interested in staying fit during their vacation, the hotel offers 3 tennis courts and a court to play basketball or volleyball. The hotel also has a fully equipped Fitness Center, a wellness center with sauna, steam bath, showers, massage cubicles (individual and for couples) and a garden with a hot tub area.  

      Lovers of water sports can also windsurf, body-board, sail, dive, snorkel and go fishing and kayaking, among other options. There is also the opportunity to do motorized water sports and deep-sea fishing, for an additional fee.

      Previous Next

      Scuba Diving

      The all inclusive Allegro Cozumel offers the best experience in and out of the water. Guests wanting to go diving can use the services provided by “Ultimate Dive Experience”, and discover the greatest coral reefs in the world, while enjoying the excellent service offered by this recently refurbished resort. Through this experience UDE guests will have access to the private reception and services of the Santa Rosa Lounge.

      What does Ultimate Dive Experience include?  

      Package benefits: 

      · One diver’s tank* per day (prior booking required) 

      · Ultimate Dive Experience exclusive ID wristband 

      · Higher-category accommodation within an exclusive section of the resort, near the beach and just two minutes from the diving shop 

      · A special hanger to dry your diving suit in your room 

      · 32-inch flat screen TV with DVD player 

      · Multimedia station in the room. Mini-bar restocked every two days 

      · Private reception with a free Internet access point 

      · Private VIP lounge exclusively for UDE guests, the Santa Rosa lounge, a place where you can socialize while enjoying ocean views. 

      · Exclusive pool area. Self-service bar (12 pm to 8 pm) 

      · Priority on bookings at the à la carte restaurants 

      · Courtesy aperitifs in the evening 

      · Additional diver’s tanks priced at US$37 

      · Free Nitrox upon presentation of a Nitrox Certificate 

      · Diving Coordinator

      Terms and Conditions:

      The Ultimate Dive Experience package is subject to availability at the time of booking and may be changed, discontinued or revoked at any point without notice. Exceptions, non-available dates, cancellation policies and other restrictions apply. We cannot be held liable for errors and missing information. Guests must hold PADI® certification or similar. Non-divers must complete their diving training on site. *Diver’s tanks are individual, non-transferable and cannot be accumulated. Limited to 1 tank per day. Equipment rental rates and access to the Marine Park are not included.

      Previous Next

      Health and Well-being

      Allegro Cozumel has a wonderful wellness center with superb facilities and luxury services. It has an excellent sauna, a hot tub and a fully equipped gym. 

      For those guests who wish to pamper their body, the spa provides a great massage service, carried out in the privacy of the cabanas, on the beach or even at sunset as a couple. 

      It also has face and body treatments with essential oils and aromatic creams that will help improve and rejuvenate the skin inside and out.

      ·Unlimited meals, snacks and drinks.

      ·Relaxation and activity pools

      ·Baths and showers

      ·Activities program for the pool and the beach

      · ATM and currency exchange (must present official identification)

      Opening hours: 9 am to 5 pm.

      Cuisine

      Bars and Restaurants 

      The 5 restaurants and 5 bars covered in the Allegro Cozumel resort’s All Inclusive program allow guests to discover an unlimited variety of culinary delights. Magnificent thematic areas to enjoy with family and friends, day or night. 

      TOPAZ 

      The Topaz restaurant offers varied theme buffets for both breakfast and dinner. 

      Opening hours: Continental breakfast: 6 am to 7 am 

      Breakfast buffet: 7:00 am to 10:30 am 

      Dinner buffet: 6:00 pm - 9:30 pm 

      SNACK BAR 

      The snack bar is perfect for quick meals thanks to the varied and delicious buffet. 

      Opening hours: noon to 5 pm 

      EL ITALIANO 

      À la carte menu with Italian cuisine specialties. Reservations required. 

      Schedule: dinner from 6:00 pm to 9:30 pm. 

      Attire: Casual pants, shirt and closed footwear for gentlemen. Skirt and blouse or dress for women. 

      EL ORIENTAL 

      This fabulous restaurant offers an á la carte menu with dishes that are the most representative of Asian cuisine. In addition, it has a sushi bar and teppanyaki grill. 

      Reservations required. Dinner schedule: 6:00 pm to 9:30 pm. 

      Attire: Casual pants, shirt and closed footwear for gentlemen. Dress, skirt and blouse for women. 

      LA TROJE 

      This restaurant has an á la carte menu that offers dishes that are most representative of Mexican cuisine. 

      Reservations required. Opening hours: 6 pm to 9:30 pm 

      Attire: Casual pants, shirt and closed footwear for gentlemen. Skirt and blouse or dress for women. 

      SPORTS BAR 

      Two independent spaces with two different environments: A lounge area and a private area with tables and stools. Cocktails, non-alcoholic beverages, juices and appetizers. 

      Opening hours: 6 pm to 1:30 am 

      DISCO BAR 

      The most fun bar has a DJ to enliven the night life. 

      Hours: from 9:00 pm to 1:30 am (Only adults after 10:00 pm) 

      POOL BAR 

      The Pool Bar is located in the area between the relaxation pool and the sports pool. 

      Opening hours: 10 am to 5 pm 

      WET BAR 

      This fabulous bar is located in the sports pool area. 

      Opening hours: 10 am to 5 pm 

      BEACH BAR 

      Located between the pool and the beach, it is ideal for spending a relaxed afternoon with nice views. 

      Opening hours: 10 am to 5 pm

The services and products listed are not part of the All Inclusive program, and guests can only deduct the indicated percentage from the total amount of the purchase of the corresponding service or product. At the time of purchasing the service or product, guests will be asked for their room number and wristband, as well as to sign a discount voucher. No additional deductions will be made to the guest's account at check-out. Resort Credit discounts cannot be redeemed for cash, neither in full nor partially, and any balance not used will not be reimbursed. The Resort Credit discounts cannot be used in conjunction with other discounts, offers or promotions. Additional restrictions may apply. Promotion is subject to changes without prior notice.         Esther v 09/07/2017 Solo travel

        “Horrible if tou think tou are going to an exotic carribean island”

        Maybe I should have read the information better, but if you want to get away from the bass booming in your ears, get earplugs, even at the beach. There is no place in the whole resort where you can get away from the bass, no outside dining possible, only in the 'sauna area' without windows inside. Trying to get you into timeshare that costs you another day of your holiday with the tric to have breakfast at the 'sister'hotel where you get stuck untill they 'let you go'. Overall, I would recommend this place for 18 years old who want to drink all day and eat burgers between the boombox. No romantic or relaxing place at all, no visibility in front of the hotel for snorkeling. Something positive: Rooms and bed brilliant!
        See full review
        PatriciaLF_13 Chardon, Ohio. 08/07/2017 Family

        “Great stay”

        We arrived at the hotel and were immediately greeted by some of the staff. We were also approached by a very nice guy that gave us some mayan calendars as a gift. At first, we thought that was nice of the hotel to give us a gift, but we then learned that those guys work for the hotel to sell you a time share, so we told them we weren't interested, and they respected that. They were always nice to us after that. However, we were told later by other guests we met, that if you book excursions with them, they're cheaper, but you need sit through a talk to sell you the time share. With that said, we really enjoyed our stay at the Allegro. We arrived at 2:30 pm and they told us our rooms weren't ready yet, that they would be ready at 3. However, when I requested for him to check if ours was ready, he did and it turns out it was. We were very pleased about this. We already knew that internet wasn't free, since we had seen it in the hotel's website. So, the people who complained about it obviously didn't read through that. We had to use the internet one day, so we ended up paying for it for our entire stay. Even though it is only supposed to work in the lobby, the internet actually worked pretty well in our room which was located across the bar in front of the kiddy pool. ROOM: Our room was very clean and modern. The shower and toilet were all new. The mattresses in our bed were very firm and comfy. We had like 6 pillows in each bed, which made it even more comfy. I read a review about you needing to keep the room at 17 C in order for it to not be humid, and it's true, but that's not the hotel's fault!! I mean, the island is hot and humid, that's inevitable. We really didn't have a problem with it. The products in the fridge are all included, and are refilled everyday. If you ask them to leave more of something, they will too. We had our room cleaned every day and the towels changed every day. RESORT: We cannot believe that there's people who have said that the grounds were not well kept. We thought the grounds were so well kept in spite of the fact that some guests were leaving plates and glasses everywhere. When we were drinking outside of our room, in the little porch, the staff would stop by and get the glasses from us. They were cleaning all the time, and we even commented that we didn't know how they did it, but they always kept the grounds so clean and well kept. There are 3 pools, the one with the slides for the kids, which is perfect for kids to be honest. The middle one which is the most calm, and the "activities pool" where they have most of the daily entertainment, and it's very close to the beach. They all have bars close by. We saw the staff cleaning the pools every day, as we would always wake up very early. RESTAURANTS AND FOOD: We didn't think the food was bad for all-inclusive standards. The food was always plenty (although we would always get there early) and even if most of it was very repetitive, they always tried to change things up. They had themed meals for dinners and breakfasts in the main restaurant, and there was always plenty of proteins, fruits and vegetables. If anything, I think that one of the things that could be improved is the amount of vegetarian options. We also tried the Mexican and Oriental restaurants. We enjoyed both, but we thought the food was not much in those, but the food was good. STAFF: We were very pleased with all the staff, they were always accommodating of our needs and requests (obviously, they weren't unreasonable). The whole staff in the restaurants were super nice. They would always offer us drinks and will always set up the high chair for my son. They would always be incredibly attentive. We really have to give kudos to Carlos, who was at the kiddy pool bar. He made the best drinks and was always super super nice. MISCELLANEOUS: It is true that everything, except for your rooms, is outside, and it is hot. But isn't that the point of a beach vacations? They also have fans everywhere, so it really isn't that bad. To be honest, I didn't really feel it. We only went to one of the kids' entertainment shows, and it was nice, but we were not counting on those shows to entertain ourselves. The beach is really nice, but there's not enough shade. It would be nice if they had umbrellas or palapas there, since the sun is pretty scorching. We knew they didn't have enough shade, since I had read it in another review, so we brought a beach cabana with us, but it was definitely not convenient. The rooms are not sound proof, obviously, so if people come by your room loudly, you will hear it. We didn't have problems with this, but there was one night that some really rude guests woke us up yelling at around 1:30 am. It is true that the weekends are busier, since there are lots of locals coming in with day passes, however they're mostly at the swimming pools and it's really not that bad. At least, it wasn't when we stayed there.
        See full review

        bealdif 07/07/2017 Friends getaway

        “Find Another Hotel”

        Let me start this review by stating that I have spent a lot of time in Mexico and Latin America and I am fluent in Spanish so communication was never an issue. We tried for HOURS to get in contact with the hotel staff to let them know that we would be arriving a day later because of flight issues and no one ever picked up the phones. When we did arrive, we were told that "it's a jungle and the phones go out sometimes", which was just an excuse. Then we had to pay for wifi, which only worked in the main lobby and was spotty in the rooms, no access by the pools or the beach. The room was horrible you had to keep the temperature at 17 degrees C (62 degrees F) otherwise the room would get so humid that the mirrors fogged up and condensation dripped from the ceiling!!! The food was on the low to average side and the property was not kept up very well. It rained most of the time we were there however the hotel has tile floors that were always wet and people were always slipping on, so dangerous!!! Because of the rain our snorkeling excursion was cancelled and we were told our refunds would be waiting for us in the morning. They didn't want to refund our friend her money saying they "already gave it to someone in her party" and ended up giving in and paying. She later found out that they paid her with a FAKE $100 BILL. This whole experience was disappointing. We complained to the staff MANY times and no one cared or did anything about it, the resort staff was unapologetic about everything. If you actually want to enjoy your vacation DON'T stay here!
        See full review

        How to get them
        How to get them Oops! Are you sure that you have spelt this correctly?

        A discount* or promotional code (also appears as “promo code”) is a combination of letters and/or numbers that gives a discount on the normal rate. If you have a discount code, enter it when booking and you will receive a discount on your booking. Once you have entered this code, the prices shown in step 1 of the booking process will already include the relevant discount. 

        The discount does not apply to prices on extras and/or extra services, neither does it apply to prices on last available rooms. Only one discount code per booking is permitted. The maximum amount of accumulated discount will be at most 25% off the rate for hotels in Latin America and at most 20% off the rate for Europe and Mediterranean hotels. It is possible to combine a discount code with a special discount** (discounts when you book multiple rooms, senior, resident, millennials, large families, etc.) and the discount for being a my Barceló client. 

        * Barceló reserves the right to accept the application of advertised discounts. 

        ** At check-in, the hotel will request to see valid official documents to verify compliance with conditions for the discount codes and special discounts. In the event of not providing valid official documents or non-compliance, the hotel reserves the right to charge the amounts that were deducted from the original reservation.

        Barceló Hotels & Resorts offer an exclusive discount for residents on the best available price on Barcelo.com.

        Terms and Conditions

        You must present your accreditation (valid ID card with address or current Certificate of Residency) on arrival at reception.

        Senior Discount

        If you are over 55, now's the time to enjoy things to the full. And to celebrate, we are offering you an additional discount on the booking price.

        Terms and Conditions Apply

        On arrival at the hotel you will be required to prove that you are at least 55 years old. For this purpose, you must present a valid identity document.
        To benefit from the discount it is essential that at least one person over 55 years old stays in the room to which the discount applies.

        Barceló Hotels & Resorts offer discounts on the best available rate for multiple room bookings at Barcelo.com.

        Please note

        This discount is applicable to those families staying at the hotel with at least 3 children under the age of 21.

        You must present proof of your age upon arrival at the hotel.
